Step 1: Identify the two numbers to use in the ratio calculation.  
• Net Profit: 1,095,371.35  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities: -81,548.37  

Step 2: Use the ratio formula:  
 Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)  

Step 3: Substitute the values:  
 Ratio = (-81,548.37) / (1,095,371.35) ≈ -0.0744  

Step 4: Round to two decimal places:  
 Ratio ≈ -0.07  

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is -0.07.
